      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:4:3:117:3",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " الْمُتَمَتِّعُ إِذَا نَظَرَ إِلَى بُيُوتِ مَكَّةَ قَطَعَ التَّلْبِيَةَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammad, from Al Halby, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The performer of <span class=\"iTxt\">Tumatto</span>, when he looks at the houses of Makkah, should cut off the <span class=\"iTxt\">Talbiyya</span>’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hammad from al-Halabiy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘One who is for al-Hajj al-Tamattu‘ (advantageous) on seeing the houses of Makkah must stop saying al-Talbiyah (here I am, O Lord, to obey Your command).”’ "
        ]
      }
    }
